ic ring.\n\nProducts: [B:20](F)(F)F.CC12CCC3C(C1CCC2=O)CCC4=C(C(=CC=C34)OC)[F:21]\n\nB is bonded to three F atoms. And F:21 is bonded to the aromatic carbon.\n\nSo the reaction center is:\n- B(20)-F(21) bond breaks\n- B(20): charge changes from - to neutral (loses one bond)\n- F(21): charge changes from + to neutral (loses one bond to B)\n\nThe reaction center is the B-F bond cleavage between atoms 20 and 21.\n\nIn reaction_edit_summary format, this would be:\n\nB(20)-F(21) bond broken; B(20): [B-]→[B]; F(21): [F+]→[F]\n\nLet me format this compactly."
